 uploaded separately.</font></li></ol><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If at this point you have decided you are not going to publish the testimonial then you can click 'Reject' to reject the approval request. This will automatically send an email to the person who asked you to approve it in the first place. You can add a reason/comment in the reply if required.</font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><br></font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you plan to approve the testimonial for publishing:</font></div><ol style=""><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>About author;</b>&nbsp;Complete the ‘About Author’ field with some generic and factual text e.g. ’Mother of one child attending BSKL’.</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Home Page and Side Bar;</b>&nbsp;Check the ‘Show on Homepage &amp; in Sidebar Block’ field as appropriate. This will also boost the testimonial in the ordering on the website.&nbsp;</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Select schools;</b>&nbsp;select the relevant school sites on which the testimonial should be displayed using the 'School Override Field'. 'No Override' means the testimonial will only be displayed on the site of the school of the parent/staff member who submitted it.</font></li><li><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><b>Publish;</b>&nbsp;If you want to publish on the group site then check the relevant checkbox. If you only want to publish on the selected school sites this will be done automatically when you 'Approve' the request (it doesn't harm to check the checkbox first either).</font></li></ol><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">If you have any questions about this process then please contact Group Admin.</font></div><div style=""><font face="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif" si